  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nBug\r\n\r\n**Current behavior**\r\nWhen you hit backspace on an `<input type=\"text\" />` and it has a value with a space before the character you're removing, the cursor jumps to the beginning of the input.\r\n\r\n**Simple Demo repro**\r\nhttps://jsfiddle.net/69z2wepo/183750/\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\nThe cursor remains at the end of the input\r\n\r\n**Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?**\r\nTested on React 16.3.2\r\nPossible related issue: https://github.com/facebook/react/issues/11827\r\n",
